When held.-The best time for holding an Institute is
when the largest number of teachers can attend, and just
before they enter upon the labors of another year. As most
schools close by the last of June, and do not reopen until
the first of September, some time during the months of July
and August is, therefore, the most appropriate.  Should any
have engagements for teaching during its session, local
directors will excuse such for the time, if the matter be
properly represented to them. In many places such teachers are not only excused, but their salaries are continued.
School managers will lose nothing by adopting this liberal
course. The winter or spring vacation, in many places, may
be a suitable time; but the convenience of teachers, and
the ability to secure competent instructors, should, in all
cases, be consulted.
