CHAPTER II.
HOW CONDUCTED.
SECTION I.-ORDER OF EXERCISES.
THE organization being completed, the subject next in
order of time, but first in importance, is the method of conducting the Institute. That the greatest possible good may
be accomplished, a well matured, systematically arranged
programme of exercises should be marked out and adhered
to as closely as possible. To assist the committee in making
out the order of daily exercises, the following for the first
day is given. In Section II will be found a division of the
branches of study taught, from which topics may be selected
for each day's exercise. Following Section II, a list of
questions in the theory and practice of teaching is given,
from which selections may be made for this department.
